attributes.Long form description: The student assembles the legs of the stool. The student places the first leg vertically on the table in a cross pattern on instructor's instruction, then he flips the feet such as if they are lying with their bottom on the table following the instructor's instructions. The student screws the middle hex nut of the leg. First, he places the baseboard and screws the legs together following the instructions, then flip the nuts on the flat part in front of it and replaces the bolt as instructed by the instructor. The student assembles the seat with the legs. He places the baseboard back on the table and then the feet on the baseboard, according to the indications given. The student screws the first screw of the legs. The instructor instructs him to turn the plastic washer over. The student screws all the screws of the leg with the stool uprights.
